               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1882" notAfter="1889" evidence="prosopography"/>
                     Metropolitan <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7830Petros">Ṗeṭros</persName>, who was in charge from <date>1882</date> to <date>1917</date>, is mentioned on 
                     <locus target="#23r #37v"/>. King <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName>, who reigned from <date>1872</date> to 
                     <date>1889</date>, is mentioned on <locus target="#24v"/>. This indicates that the manuscript was written between <date>1882</date> and <date>1889</date>.
                     The name of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12962WaldaMa">Walda Māryām</persName> is frequently mentioned in the supplication formulas throughout the manuscript. 
                     The name is overwritten in a secondary hand over other effaced names. This strongly suggests that he was either a later owner or donor of the manuscript.
                  </origin>
               </history>
          
